34:09.003 --> 34:10.700
She might give you
the benefit of the doubt

34:10.874 --> 34:15.444
if your seven looks like a one
with a fancy tail, right?

34:15.618 --> 34:18.317
The same with a two and a six.

34:18.491 --> 34:20.188
Right? Keep her guessing.

34:20.362 --> 34:22.799
That means you'll have two
or three horses in every race.

34:22.973 --> 34:24.671
Isn't that cheating?

34:24.845 --> 34:27.500
No, well, I'd call it
spread betting.

34:27.674 --> 34:31.156
And if it gets you moved up by
one seat to bask in the light

34:31.330 --> 34:33.549
of her glory,
then you're off to the races.

34:33.723 --> 34:36.030
But sure there's only one
right answer.

34:36.204 --> 34:37.771
If that were true, son,
people wouldn't be

34:37.945 --> 34:40.208
blowing themselves up
all over this town.

34:44.430 --> 34:47.346
I think my da wants us
to leave Belfast.

34:52.090 --> 34:54.222
What do you want?

34:54.396 --> 34:58.879
Every night, before I go to
sleep, when I say my prayers,

34:59.053 --> 35:01.664
I ask God if he'd fix it
so that when I wake up

35:01.838 --> 35:04.885
in the morning, I'm the best
footballer in the world.

35:05.059 --> 35:07.453
And then I also ask him as well

35:07.627 --> 35:10.238
that when I grow up,
can I marry Catherine.

35:10.412 --> 35:12.153
Even if she loves Ronnie Boyd.

35:12.327 --> 35:14.808
But she could still see him,
but she'd marry me.

35:14.982 --> 35:16.679
That's what I want.

35:24.644 --> 35:26.428
LIBERTY VALANCE: You looking
for trouble, Doniphon?

35:26.602 --> 35:28.778
DONIPHON:
You aim to help me find some?

35:30.258 --> 35:31.564
What's the matter?

35:31.738 --> 35:33.392
Everybody in this country
kill crazy?!

35:33.566 --> 35:34.567
Here!

35:35.611 --> 35:37.657
VALANCE:
Show's over for now.

35:39.485 --> 35:41.269
DONIPHON:
Try it, Liberty.

35:42.140 --> 35:43.663
Just try it.

35:43.837 --> 35:45.317
STODDARD: What right
do you have to interfere?

35:45.491 --> 35:46.970
It was me he tripped.

35:47.145 --> 35:48.842
I have to keep those boys
where I can see 'em.

35:49.016 --> 35:50.670
PA: Well, I can't come home
every weekend, for God's sake.

35:50.844 --> 35:52.541
Well, if you can't be bothered,
well, then don't blame me

35:52.715 --> 35:54.195
-for what them boys get up to.
-That's not what I'm saying.

35:54.369 --> 35:56.154
-You can't just throw
that one... -

35:59.026 --> 35:59.983
MAN:
Right, that's 6:00 a.m., fellas.

36:00.158 --> 36:02.029
